it=\r\n comes with risks. The former approach is safer and one loses nothing in it=\r\n. Similarly, one can progress towards complete Self-realization without any=\r\n out of body experiences. These are not my word&#39;s, but Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s=\r\n words to Lord Rama.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Secondly, one does not get something without =\r\nwanting it and putting sufficient effort towards it. One may have deeply de=\r\nsired a Kundalini rise in a previous life and may have put enough effort. A=\r\ns a result, one may be getting it now. But one may be unprepared (and ironi=\r\ncally may not even want it!) when it comes in this life.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;As you do=\r\n sadhana, try not to fancy too many specific desires. Nature has a delay me=\r\nchanism in granting your desires (because of constraints on what Nature can=\r\n give you right now, arising from YOUR OWN previous actions). So Nature som=\r\netimes gives you what you want LATE, when you no longer want it or want som=\r\nething else. For example, one may pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole life an=\r\nd be born as a rich but very sick man in next life. One may not enjoy that =\r\nwealth and pray whole life for health. In the life after that, one may be v=\r\nery healthy, but not have any knowledge or money. In another case, one may =\r\ndeeply desire to act in a famous film. One may be reborn as a tiger or a do=\r\ng and act in a famous film, but not really enjoy that experience. Basically=\r\n, people keep going in circles through various lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; some=\r\nthing they are &quot;missing&quot;.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kundalini, if one=\r\n deeply desires an out of body experience given by a rising Kundalini and o=\r\nne&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from having it in THIS life, one may be =\r\nborn in next life with this specific desire destined to fructify (if there =\r\nis enough karmik force behind it).\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Kundali=\r\nni rise is not necessarily scary or painful, if one is well-prepared in ter=\r\nms of attitude and detachment.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mo=\r\nuse trap. I went to free it and it panicked so badly and started to shake v=\r\niolently. I went to save it from a certain slow death and it was scared tha=\r\nt I would kill it!\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;We are like that chipmunk, glued to the mouse t=\r\nrap called this body-mind complex and scared of being rescued from a certai=\r\nn slow death!\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;If our ideas about who we are (viz this current body=\r\n-mind complex) are incorrect and if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras=\r\n say, won&#39;t a complete realization of that at some stage involve stepping o=\r\nut of this body-mind complex, without being scared?\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 =\r\n*\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Kundalini rise after most undesirable conditioning is overcome, =\r\nis far better than Kundalini rise forced when some really undesirable condi=\r\ntioning is still left in one&#39;s system.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;When one transcends one pro=\r\nblematic notion about who one is and what one needs, another notion that la=\r\ny buried deeper in consciousness may spring to the surface and torment one.=\r\n If one overcomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be another notion i=\r\nn one&#39;s body-mind complex that one&#39;s awareness clings on to (e.g. a great d=\r\noctor, a great leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc). As an extreme e=\r\nxample, if one person had a hidden deep desire to be a great soul who rescu=\r\nes the world, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y who will rescu=\r\ne the world now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!) deeply clings =\r\nto any such notion, it can cause havoc. The person may show some signs of p=\r\nrogress and yet remain in ignorance and get stuck badly.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;An awaken=\r\ned Kundalini in a system with undesirable conditioning may accentuate one&#39;s=\r\n weaknesses and wrong notions heavily and cause serious psychiatric and spi=\r\nritual problems.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;The best approach I reco=\r\nmmend is to NOT think in terms of Kundalini and its rise. Just do sadhana, =\r\novercome your weaknesses and improve your detachment over time. Again, I wa=\r\nnt to emphasize that detachment is not disgust or distaste for life/things/=\r\npeople around you. Disgust is the other side of coin of attachment. It is a=\r\n negative attachment.=C2=A0\n&gt;Don&#39;t worry about whether your Kundalini rises=\r\n or not. Worry about whether you are able to resist 6 internal enemies (sha=\r\ndripus) and 8 bondages (ashta pashas) or not. If your ability to resist the=\r\nm is increasing, you are making progress. EVEN IF your Kundalini is fast as=\r\nleep, you are still making progress. When you completely overcome them, Kun=\r\ndalini (your self-awareness) will automatically ascend to the top and meet =\r\nHer Lord (true Self).\n&gt;=C2=A0*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;One word on surrender=\r\ning to a personal deity. Though true surrender is helpful, most people do n=\r\not have it. They simply do business with god. Though people may be offended=\r\n by my words, this is the plain and bare fact.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&quot;I want X, I will p=\r\nray to you and please give it to me&quot;, &quot;I am scared of Kundalini rise, I wil=\r\nl pray to you and please protect me&quot; - all this is just a business deal. Th=\r\nere is something you want and you ask god for it. True surrender has no pla=\r\nce for agendas, desires, demands or expectations. True surrender is losing =\r\noneself in one&#39;s fascination for the qualities of Lord. True surrender is a=\r\nccepting anything Lord throws one&#39;s way (whether it is pleasurable or highl=\r\ny painful) as Lord&#39;s prasad and accepting it gratefully. True surrender is =\r\nthinking of Lord with fascination and pleasure, even in the face of (and du=\r\nring) Death.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;If one without true surrender and with many desires a=\r\nnd wrong notions experiences a Kundalini rise, one may still be trapped, de=\r\nspite thinking of a personal god. It is not that god does not want to &quot;prot=\r\nect&quot; one as said below. It is not about protecting or endangering. If you g=\r\no back to my &quot;chipmunk glued to mouse trap&quot; example above, I was trying to =\r\nprotect it, but it was scared. Similarly, one&#39;s conditioning makes one *run=\r\n away* from God&#39;s protection! God&#39;s protection may seem to a conditioned mi=\r\nnd like grave danger that one should run away from!\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 =\r\n*\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Whether through the path of wisdom or surrender, develop dispass=\r\nion and detachment. Realize that all this is temporary and can be taken awa=\r\ny anytime. Enjoy it while you have and keep doing your best, but be prepare=\r\nd to lose everything anytime. Only detachment and a very light mental condi=\r\ntioning (very light desires, dislikes etc) can protect one as one&#39;s Kundali=\r\nni rises to meet True Self. Heavy conditioning and impurities in one&#39;s nadi=\r\ns will distract rising Kundalini (self-awareness) and stop Her from meeting=\r\n True Self.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;The real key is how light your conditioning is.\n&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0\n&gt;Best regards,Narasimha--------Astrology & Spirituality Resources: http=\r\n://www.vedicastrologer.org/\n&gt;--------\n&gt;\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;&gt;_____________________=\r\n___________\n&gt;&gt;From: Leela Sastry 