zation without any out of body experiences. These are not=\r\n my word&#39;s, but Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s words to Lord Rama.&lt;BR&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Secon=\r\ndly, one does not get something without wanting it and putting sufficient e=\r\nffort towards it. One may have deeply desired a Kundalini rise in a previou=\r\ns life and may have put enough effort. As a result, one may be getting it n=\r\now. But one may be unprepared (and ironically may not even want it!) when i=\r\nt comes in this life.&lt;BR&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;As you do sadhana, try not to fancy too =\r\nmany specific desires. Nature has a delay mechanism in granting your desire=\r\ns (because of constraints on what\n Nature can give you right now, arising f=\r\nrom YOUR OWN previous actions). So Nature sometimes gives you what you want=\r\n LATE, when you no longer want it or want something else. For example, one =\r\nmay pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole life and be born as a rich but very s=\r\nick man in next life. One may not enjoy that wealth and pray whole life for=\r\n health. In the life after that, one may be very healthy, but not have any =\r\nknowledge or money. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN id=3Dyiv1491792485yui_3_7_2_19_13620678466=\r\n19_141&gt;In another case, one may deeply desire to act in a famous film. One =\r\nmay be reborn as a tiger or a dog and act in a famous film, but not really =\r\nenjoy that experience. Basically, people &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN id=3Dyiv1491792485yui=\r\n_3_7_2_19_1362067846619_141&gt;keep going in circles through various lives, al=\r\nways &quot;seeking&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.&lt;BR&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Anyway, coming ba=\r\nck to Kundalini, if one deeply desires an out of body experience given by a=\r\n rising Kundalini and one&#39;s\n previous karmas constrain one from having it i=\r\nn THIS life, one may be born in next life with this specific desire destine=\r\nd to fructify (if there is enough karmik force behind it).&lt;BR&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR