deranged kundalini. Many people=\r\n we call mentally ill describe themselves as having a spiritual crisis, or =\r\nunwanted spontaneous kundalini awakening- this has triggered interest and r=\r\nesearch into this topic in mainstream psychiatry. Unfortunately these patie=\r\nnts are not well-understood by western medicine, and as we have no treatmen=\r\nts for deranged\n kundalini, we struggle to help them. Many yogis try to for=\r\ncibly waken the kundalini. My experience with this lady confirmed my feelin=\r\ng that kundalini should not be forcibly wakened. This woman wants to kill h=\r\nerself at times because the suffering from the deranged energy is so bad. S=\r\nhe feels it will consume her, and it is something she cannot escape from. I=\r\n wondered what solution there could be to her problem. The logical one was =\r\nto pray to the Divine Mother, who manifests as the kundalini to relieve the=\r\n suffering of this woman- and either cure her, or give her the strength to =\r\nbear this. May I request that the good samaritans among you pray for her, a=\r\nnd for others like her (whom we may not know of)- their suffering really is=\r\n pitiable. And let us be careful in our sadhana so as not to end up in this=\r\n situation ourselves. Perhaps this is why the bhakti marga is the safest. I=\r\nt is perhaps safest to say &quot;let me be your instrument&quot; and leave the kundal=\r\nini\n rising bit to God&#39;s will. Om Dum Durgayai Namaha Aparna &lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/=\r\nDIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/DI=\r\nV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/=\r\nDIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&lt;WBR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/div&gt;=\r\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;\r\n---1